Today is Friday! You can’t be more excited, especially as another month begins. Then (in whispers), if you are a salary earner… let’s not say everything. You probably might have heard of banga soup. Try cooking it this weekend. It is said to be indigenous to the people of Delta State, in Nigeria – unlike the banga stew cooked in South Eastern states and served with white boiled rice or yam. This one is best served with starch or eba. However, both the banga stew and soup are made with similar ingredients. Ingredients – Serving about 12 Persons. You should use crushed dried beletientien leaves, also called atama leaf in Efik or thinly sliced bitter leaves. From allnigerianfoods. Read More: Classification of heart-healthy nutrients